# Medical Presentation Framework — .gitignore

# Development backups and superseded drafts. See MAINTAINER.md for what
# this folder is and why it's excluded.
not-used/

# Backup files anywhere in the tree (safe-file-operations.md convention:
# {file}.backup-YYYYMMDD-HHMM.{ext})
*.backup-*

# OS / editor noise
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
*.swp
*~
.vscode/
.idea/

# Python build artefacts (in case scripts get added later)
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.venv/
venv/

# Live working presentation projects — keep the framework repo clean of
# patient-adjacent or in-progress decks. Uncomment lines that match the
# topic-folder names you use, or add your own. The README's example layout
# uses rotation names like the ones below.
# Internal Medicine/
# Rheumatology/
# Nephrology/
# Cardiology/
# Infectious Diseases/
# Endocrinology/
# Journal Club/
# Case Discussions/

# User theme files (under theme/) — track only the README, exclude the
# user's own theme palettes which are often institution-specific.
theme/*
!theme/README.md

# User PPTX templates (under templates/) — track only the README, exclude
# the user's own template files which are often institution-confidential.
templates/*
!templates/README.md

# Personal files at workspace root (e.g., personal theme drafts, notes)
# matching the *_personal pattern.
*_personal.md

# Local-only maintainer files — not part of the public framework.
# AGENTS.md is a stub pointing at CLAUDE.md for non-Cowork agents;
# MAINTAINER.md is the maintainer's private dev guide. Both stay on the
# maintainer's machine only.
AGENTS.md
MAINTAINER.md
